                                                        <div id="section-10" class="detail-content coursedessside">
                  <h2 class="heading-new"><span>FAQs</span></h2>
                                    <div class="examsdetailscnt">
                                     <p><strong><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Some of the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) related to the exam of IBPS-PO are as follows:</span></strong></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: Who conducts the PO exam?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: IBPS (Institute of Banking Personnel Selection) conducts the PO exam.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: Is the examination bilingual?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: Yes. The paper is available both in Hindi and English.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: Is there a fixed time in which a section has to be attempted?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: Not in prelims. There is a stipulated time for each section in the mains examination.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: Is there any negative marking?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: Yes.0.25 marks will be deducted for every incorrect answer.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: Will the exam be conducted in Online or Offline Mode?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: The exam will be conducted in the Online mode for both Prelims and Main.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: What is the upper and lower age limit for the Exam?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: The minimum age limit for the exam is 20 years and maximum age limit is 30 years.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: What is the Educational Qualification required for the IBPS PO exam?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: Graduation degree in any discipline is required for the getting eligible for the IBPS PO exam.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: I have 42% in Graduation. Can I apply for IBPS PO exam?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: Yes, there is no minimum criteria for graduation percentage. You need to be a graduate from a recognized University.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: Is there a sectional cut-off in IBPS PO exam?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: Yes, there is a sectional cut-off in IBPS PO exam and the candidate needs to secure the minimum cutoff for all the sections.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: What post will be given after selection in IBPS PO?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: The selected candidates will be given the post of Probationary Officer/Management Trainee.</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{color: "rgb(41, 105, 176)", "font-size": "14px"}}>Q: I am 18 years old. Can I apply to IBPS Po?</span></p><p dir="ltr"><span style={{"font-size": "14px"}}>Ans: No, the minimum age limit of IBPS PO exam is 20 years.</span></p>										</div>
                </div>
